Subject: [PATCH 53/64] web-app: estimated time-to-read on the unread badge
 (experimental)

Show roughly how long a chat's unread messages take to read (e.g. "~4 min")
next to the unread counter in the chat list. Off by default, opt in under
Settings -> Advanced -> Experimental features (issue #113).

The estimate is computed client-side per chat: word count of unread bodies at
200 wpm, plus a flat 10 s per media message; voice/audio messages use their
recorded duration instead. Only a padded window of the newest <=100 messages
is fetched (unread = state IN_FRESH within it); if the unread count exceeds
the window the estimate is scaled linearly and capped at "10+ min", so massive
backlogs never pull full bodies. Results are cached per chat, keyed on the
fresh-message counter, which changes exactly when the unread set does.

Pure estimate math lives in readTimeEstimate.ts with a mocha test
(src/tests/readTimeEstimate.test.ts); fetching and the hook sit in
ChatListItem.tsx. Settings key experimentalUnreadReadTime mirrors the
existing experimentalCompletionMenu flag.

